      <div class="work-feature-list">
        <article class="work-case work-case--primary">
          <div class="work-case__summary">
            <span class="work-case__index">01</span>
            <h3>Bezel</h3>
            <p>The operating system behind everything.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="work-case__body">
            <p>Bezel tracks work, assigns ownership, enforces decisions, and verifies outcomes. Agents do not wait for instructions. They pull work, complete it, and prove it.</p>
            <p>It holds the state of every task, every dependency, and every decision. Work is not pushed down from a central controller. Agents claim work based on readiness, execute it, and move it forward.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>What was planned</li>
              <li>What was claimed</li>
              <li>What was completed</li>
              <li>What evidence supports it</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="work-proof-line">Proof today: Bezel is actively running Dreamborn. Every workflow, handoff, and output passes through it.</p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="work-case">
          <div class="work-case__summary">
            <span class="work-case__index">02</span>
            <h3>Dreamborn Studios</h3>
            <p>Where humans stay in control.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="work-case__body">
            <p>Studios are the control layer for an AI-native company. They separate judgment from execution.</p>
            <p>Humans decide what should happen. Agents handle how it gets done.</p>
            <div class="work-studio-grid">
              <div>
                <strong>Ops Studio</strong>
                <span>Live operations, fleet health, workflows, and decisions in motion.</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <strong>Dev Studio</strong>
                <span>Project intake, specifications, policies, and readiness before work is claimed.</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <strong>Marketing Studio</strong>
                <span>Campaigns, content, visual production, voice pass, and publishing.</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="work-proof-line">Proof today: Dreamborn operations move through Studios. No work starts without clarity. No work ships without review.</p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="work-case">
          <div class="work-case__summary">
            <span class="work-case__index">03</span>
            <h3>Dreamborn.ai</h3>
            <p>The company, in public.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="work-case__body">
            <p>Dreamborn.ai is not just a website. It is the external layer of the company.</p>
            <p>It shows how the company works, not just what it says. The site includes the Work page, System page, Thinking archive, founder pitch, brand system, org chart, marketecture, and visitor agent experience.</p>
            <p>This is the opposite of a static site. It evolves with the company.</p>
            <p class="work-proof-line">Proof today: Dreamborn.ai is generated, maintained, and updated through the same operating system that runs the business.</p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="work-case">
          <div class="work-case__summary">
            <span class="work-case__index">04</span>
            <h3>KnowledgeVault</h3>
            <p>Capturing what companies actually know.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="work-case__body">
            <p>KnowledgeVault turns product and field knowledge into usable, structured assets.</p>
            <p>For manufacturers and distributors, the real knowledge often sits in people, not systems. KnowledgeVault captures that knowledge directly.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>SKU-level coverage tracking</li>
              <li>Expert onboarding workflows</li>
              <li>Voice-based capture</li>
              <li>Quality scoring and validation</li>
              <li>Product dashboards</li>
              <li>Monetization pathways</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="work-proof-line">Proof today: KnowledgeVault is built and being deployed as a working system, not a concept.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
